id: pm-y5u0
title: Deduplicate bundled package runtime option parsing helpers
description: "Duplicate audit 2026-05-22: readStringOption/readBooleanOption and adjacent SDK-runtime loading boilerplate are repeated across bundled package runtimes. Exact clones show in packages/pm-linked-test-adapters/extensions/linked-test-adapters/runtime.ts:67 and packages/pm-guide-shell/extensions/guide-shell/runtime.ts:99, with the same helper shape also present in pm-governance-audit and pm-search-advanced plus committed JS twins. This is not covered by pm-why9, which is scoped to CLI parser blocks, item casts, runtime schema defaults, and update.ts field tables. Fix by moving package runtime option readers/load helpers into a shared package-runtime helper that built-in packages can import or generate from, while preserving standalone package behavior and JS/TS packaging expectations."
type: Chore
status: open
priority: 2
tags[3]: code-quality,dedup,packages
created_at: "2026-05-22T18:53:54.877Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-22T18:53:54.877Z"
author: codex-duplicate-audit
acceptance_criteria: "A single shared helper owns package runtime string/boolean option parsing and common runtime-load failure handling; linked-test-adapters, guide-shell, governance-audit, and search-advanced runtimes no longer carry copy-pasted helper bodies; package smoke tests and pnpm build stay green."
parent: pm-rnpb
